    "Name": "Pendragon",
    "Details": "Conceptualised as a long range support platform, the Pendragon was a result of House Davion’s Jihad era MUSE programs. A 95-ton mech, the Pendragon is built around a 285-rated XL Engine and is loosely based on the Templar OmniMech. The Pendragon PDR-1X is the original MUSE prototype utilising a mix of Clan and IS technology. A pair of Clan-spec LRM-20’s along with a pair of standard LRM-20's provide range firepower, while an ER PPC with capacitor and a trio of Clan ER Medium Lasers provide closer ranged firepower. A C3i computer provides combat electronic handling.<br><br>X-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
